The Kogi State Government, on Tuesday, said it has appointed three commissioners. This was contained in a statement by Mohammed Onogwu, the Chief Press Secretary to the governor, he named the three Commissioner-designates as; Kingsley Femi Fanwo, Former Commissioner for Information and Communications from Mopa Muro LGA; Dr Zakeri Usman (Dekina LGA) and Engineer Mohammed Ihiezue Abdulmutalab (Okene LGA). He said the appointment was an effort by the state government to rejig his administration for better performance. He noted that he has sent their names to the state House of Assembly for screening and confirmation.